  <source>Hannover Medical School</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to show that the incidence of sternal wound infections at day 30
      after cardiac surgery is 50% lower with the additional use of Daptomycin on top of a standard
      antibiotic prophylaxis as compared to the standard antibiotic prophylaxis alone.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
